==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc}} {{term|sc=polytonic|σάββατον|tr=sabbaton||Sabbath}} < Hebrew {{term|sc=Hebr|שבת|tr=shabbat||Sabbath}}.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# The [[Biblical]] seventh [[day]] of the [[week]], observed as a day of rest in [[Judaism]], [[Advent|Seventh-day Adventism]], or [[Baptism|Seventh Day Baptism]], starting at [[sundown]] on [[Friday]] till sundown on [[Saturday]].
# [[Sunday]], observed throughout the majority of [[Christianity]] as a day of rest.(Not Biblical)
# [[Friday]], observed in [[Islam]] as a day of rest.
# A meeting of [[witch]]es at [[midnight]].

